        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 7:47PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 747 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near McFadden to near Brinkley. Movement was
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cody, Cottonwood Corner, Fitzgerald Crossing, Wheatley, New Castle,
Brushy Lake, Round Pond, McElroy, Coldwater, Cherry Valley, Ball
Point, Gill, Hawkins, River Front, Village Creek State Park, Tilton,
Duvall, Four Forks, Burnt Cane, and Four Gums.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
eastern Arkansas.</instruction>
